By AM-GM,
\[abcda^{-1}c^{-1}d^{1/4} \le ab^2 cd.\]Since $a + b + c + d = 10,$ both sides above equal $10.$ Equality occurs when $a=b=c=d=10 / 4 = \tfrac{5}{2},$ so the minimum possible value is $\left(\tfrac{5}{2}\right)^2 \cdot (\tfrac{5}{2}) = \boxed{\tfrac{625}{16}}.$
The answer is: \frac{625}{16}
